{"tid":2025869,"cid":5,"subCid":10,"title":"美國商會：供應鏈遷出中國過度，可能會損害美國經濟","createTime":"2020-05-20T14:21:04.000Z","updateTime":"2020-05-20T14:36:31.000Z","uid":75656,"like":1,"dislike":13,"uniUserReply":8,"replies":[{"pid":"2ebc8e4430f9340a962ae5b18da2f510e79d16a8","tid":2025869,"uid":75656,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-05-20T14:21:04.000Z","msg":"WASHINGTON (Reuters) - The U.S. Chamber of Commerce on Tuesday warned the U.S. government against overdoing a major effort underway to rip U.S. supply chains out of China in the wake of the coronavirus pandemic, saying such moves could harm the economy.<br />\n<br />\n&ldquo;Protecting the resiliency of our supply chain doesn&rsquo;t have to mean reshoring all production in the United States,&rdquo; Chamber Chief Executive Thomas Donohue told an online conference.<br />\n<br />\nHe said there may be a need in future to increase domestic production in some industries &ldquo;but there will also need to continue to be a huge place in the U.S. economy for a global supply chain.&rdquo;<br />\n<br />\nThe U.S. Chamber and other groups say moving production facilities to the United States from overseas will be costly and time consuming, and stockpiling essential supplies would be more cost effective.<br />\n<br />\n<a href=\"https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-supply-chains/u-s-chamber-ceo-warns-against-overdoing-it-with-production-reshoring-effort-idUSKBN22V2VO?il=0\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Farticle%2Fus-health-coronavirus-supply-chains%2Fu-s-chamber-ceo-warns-against-overdoing-it-with-production-reshoring-effort-idUSKBN22V2VO%3Fil%3D0&d=74ULG85bswSWcCYhLq3krEYzBSotcsoJ75UENuGtOl4%3D&h=8521811c\" data-ef-url=\"https://embed.lih.kg/frame?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Farticle%2Fus-health-coronavirus-supply-chains%2Fu-s-chamber-ceo-warns-against-overdoing-it-with-production-reshoring-effort-idUSKBN22V2VO%3Fil%3D0&h=d8493f35\" target=\"